      "content": "Quantum entanglement is a phenomenon where two or more particles become linked, so the state of one particle instantly influences the state of the other, no matter how far apart they are. It's like having a pair of magical, invisible gloves that always match. If you put on one glove, the other glove will instantly know and change to match. This is different from classical correlation, where objects are connected through a chain of cause and effect, like a line of dominoes falling one after another. In entanglement, it's as if the gloves are connected by a mystical force that defies the usual rules of space and time.",
